If I understand you correctly, you want to compose a multipart request manually from an HTTP/REST console. The multipart format is simple; a brief introduction can be found [in the HTML 4.01 spec][1]. You need to come up with a boundary, which is a string not found in the content, let‚Äôs say `HereGoes`. You set request header `Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=HereGoes`. Then this should be a valid request body:

    --HereGoes
    Content-Disposition: form-data; name=&quot;myJsonString&quot;
    Content-Type: application/json

    {&quot;foo&quot;: &quot;bar&quot;}
    --HereGoes
    Content-Disposition: form-data; name=&quot;photo&quot;
    Content-Type: image/jpeg
    Content-Transfer-Encoding: base64

    &lt;...JPEG content in base64...&gt;
    --HereGoes--

[1]: http://www.w3.org/TR/html401/interact/forms.html#h-17.13.4.2

